v0.1.0: walk-forward validation — 3 assets confirmed out-of-sample

Walk-forward validation (exp-008) proves the EMA crossover signal is genuine
on SPY, QQQ, and GLD. The HMM regime filter, while useful for in-sample
exploration, overfits and does not survive out-of-sample testing.

Walk-forward validated results (5y train / 1y test, rolling):
- SPY EMA 8/21, no filter: Sharpe 0.88, DD 16.4%, 35 trades
- QQQ EMA 8/25, no filter: Sharpe 0.96, DD 17.6%, 33 trades
- GLD EMA 7/18, no filter: Sharpe 0.85, DD 18.7%, 33 trades

Key finding: the unfiltered EMA crossover has real edge on diversified,
structurally trending assets with moderate volatility. Single stocks
(MSFT, AAPL) and narrow indices (DIA) fail OOS due to uncontrollable
drawdown without the HMM, which itself doesn't generalize.

Added:
- backtest/walk_forward.py — rolling train/test harness
- data/regime.py — split into fit_regime_model() + predict_regimes()
- scripts/run_wf_tuning.py — targeted WF parameter sweeps

Updated: README, CHANGELOG, EXPERIMENT_LOG with OOS results and analysis.
